{{Infobox software | name = Darwin Streaming Server | logo = | screenshot = | caption = 65 | collapsible = | author = [[Apple Inc.]] | developer = [[Apple Inc.]] | released = March 16, 1999 | latest release version = 6.0.3 | latest release date = May 10, 2007 | latest preview version = | latest preview date = | programming language = | operating system = [[OS X]], [[Linux]], [[Windows]] | platform = | size = | language = | status = | genre = [[Real Time Streaming Protocol|RTSP]] [[Server (computing)|server]] | license = [[Apple Public Source License]] | website = http://dss.macosforge.org/ }}
'''Darwin Streaming Server''' (DSS) was the first open sourced [[Real-time Transport Protocol|RTP]]/[[Real Time Streaming Protocol|RTSP]] streaming server.<ref name="Sherry2013">{{cite book|author=Phil Sherry|title=Foundation Mac OS X Web Development|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GUgnCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA278|date=11 November 2013|publisher=Apress|isbn=978-1-4302-5133-0|pages=278–}}</ref> It was released March 16, 1999 and is a fully featured [[Real Time Streaming Protocol|RTSP]]/[[Real-time Transport Protocol|RTP]] media streaming server capable of streaming a variety of media types including [[H.264/MPEG-4 AVC]], [[MPEG-4 Part 2]] and [[3GP]].
==Development== Developed by [[Apple Computer|Apple]], it is the open source equivalent of [[QuickTime Streaming Server]], and is based on its code.
==Ports== The initial DSS source code release compiled only on [[OS X]], but external developers quickly ported the code to [[Linux]], [[FreeBSD]], [[Solaris (operating system)|Solaris]],<ref>[http://www.nbl.fi/~nbl97/solaris/media/streaming/ Darwin Streaming Server on Solaris]</ref> [[Tru64 Unix]], [[Mac OS 9]] and [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]].
Source code is available as a release download or as development code via [[Concurrent Versions System|CVS]].
